subSubSection.paragraph:
Internal and microstructural characters.
The radial shield is a small sub-rounded plate. The adradial genital plate is absent. Arm spine articulation belongs to the double-opening 
type
(
Figs 43A–C
). The muscle opening is placed on a distinct round or elongated elevation, some articulations slightly ribbed distally. The nerve opening is placed laterally below the level of the muscle opening. Ventralmost spine articulations have a rounded shape (
Fig. 43C
). Vertebrae rather long proximally, not keeled and with well developed zygospondylous articulation (
Fig. 43I
). The vertebral dorsal median groove is slightly distinct. Podial basins are large (
Fig. 43H
).
